Generally, it's like that for every language that is not your own. I'm 
Polish and these words seem quite normal for me because I've been speaking 
the language since I was born. It is quite funny to see how people break 
their tongues over these words, however, it doesn't mean that it doesn't 
make sense like some said. Some native English speakers should have in mind 
that some non-biligual people have the same problem with English as the 
people in the video with Polish city names. So, next time anyone tries to 
make fun about "foreigner accent" while speaking English, think about this 
video and how it is the exact same situation! :)﻿
